# Project Architecture

This Electron application uses Vite and follows a specific structure for organization:

## Core Configuration Files
- [electron.vite.config.ts](mdc:electron.vite.config.ts) - Main Vite configuration
- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Dependencies and scripts
- [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) - TypeScript configuration

## Main Application Structure
- `/src/main` - Electron main process code
- `/src/preload` - Preload scripts for secure IPC
- `/src/renderer` - Frontend UI code
  - `/src/renderer/src/components` - Reusable React components
  - `/src/renderer/src/pages` - Application pages/routes
  - `/src/renderer/src/services` - Core services (review, storage, clipboard)
  - `/src/renderer/src/ui` - UI component library
  - `/src/renderer/src/data/templates` - Pre-built card templates

## Key Features
- Global shortcut (Ctrl + Shift + X) for quick card creation
- LocalStorage-based data persistence (future PostgreSQL sync planned)
- Internationalization support under `/src/renderer/src/i18n`
- TailwindCSS for styling
- Electron auto-updates via GitHub releases

